Entries.Title: TV5
Entries.Description: TV5 is a major Philippine television network offering a mix of local and international programming, including news, entertainment, and sports.

Entries.Title: A2Z (ABS-CBN)
Entries.Description: A2Z is a Philippine free-to-air blocktime broadcast television network based in Quezon City, with its studios located in Ortigas Center, Pasig. It serves as a flagship property of ZOE Broadcasting Network, the broadcast media arm of Jesus Is Lord Church Worldwide, in partnership with ABS-CBN Corporation as its main content provider through a blocktime agreement.

Entries.Title: Jurassic World Rebirth
Entries.Description: Five years after the events of Jurassic World Dominion, covert operations expert Zora Bennett is contracted to lead a skilled team on a top-secret mission to secure genetic material from the world's three most massive dinosaurs. When Zora's operation intersects with a civilian family whose boating expedition was capsized, they all find themselves stranded on an island where they come face-to-face with a sinister, shocking discovery that's been hidden from the world for decades.

Entries.Title: Jurassic World Camp Cretaceous
Entries.Description: Six teens attending an adventure camp on the opposite side of Isla Nublar must band together to survive when dinosaurs wreak havoc on the island.

Episodes.Title: Camp Cretaceous
Episodes.Description: After waiting his whole life to see dinosaurs, lucky Darius wins the chance to join five other campers on Isla Nublar for a once-in-a-lifetime adventure.

Episodes.Title: Secrets
Episodes.Description: With the rest of the crew off visiting a genetics lab, Kenji sneaks Darius into the park's top-secret underbelly â€” and straight into danger.

Episodes.Title: The Cattle Drive
Episodes.Description: The campers hop into their Gyrospheres to help move a dinosaur herd toward fresh grazing lands. But an incoming storm stirs up unexpected trouble.

Episodes.Title: Things Fall Apart
Episodes.Description: Darius remembers the promise he made to his dad. Elsewhere on the island, the campers find themselves face-to-face with a newly freed threat.

Episodes.Title: Happy Birthday, Eddie!
Episodes.Description: After a close encounter with the Indominus, the gang seeks shelter in the genetics lab, where a strange scientist reveals the truth about Dr. Wu.

Episodes.Title: Welcome to Jurassic World
Episodes.Description: Sammy's secret shocks everyone â€” but there's no time for anger when an accident unleashes a flock of Pteranodons and forces the crew below ground.

Episodes.Title: Last Day of Camp
Episodes.Description: The campers leave the Mosasaurus lagoon and fight their way onto the monorail â€¦ where Ben gets a chance to face his fears.

Episodes.Title: End of the Line
Episodes.Description: It's a race against time as the campers make their way to the main dock to catch the last ferry leaving the island. But what if they're too late?

Episodes.Title: A Beacon of Hope
Episodes.Description: Still stranded on the island â€” and still reeling from the apparent loss of Ben â€” the campers make a last-ditch attempt at rescue by sending out an SOS.

Episodes.Title: The Art of Chill
Episodes.Description: Darius and Sammy face a moral dilemma while searching the park for supplies. The campers start building a new treehouse. Brooklynn sees something odd.

Episodes.Title: The Watering Hole
Episodes.Description: Brooklynn, Sammy and Yasmina team up to investigate strange noises in the park. Elsewhere, Darius and Kenji go exploring and witness a majestic sight.

Episodes.Title: Salvation
Episodes.Description: A bonfire in the distance signals that the campers have company: a pair of posh eco-tourists and their disgruntled security guy. But can they be trusted?

Episodes.Title: Brave
Episodes.Description: The campers reunite with a long-lost friend, who shares an inspiring story â€” then reveals that Mitch, Tiff and Hap aren't who they seem.

Episodes.Title: Misguided
Episodes.Description: Darius must make a difficult choice to save Sammy and Yasmina. Meanwhile, the remaining campers are trying to decide if Hap is a friend... or a foe.

Episodes.Title: Step One
Episodes.Description: Brooklynn, Ben, Kenji and Yasmina work to uncover a secret and restore power to the park as Darius leads Mitch and Tiff straight into a T. rex trap.

Episodes.Title: Chaos Theory
Episodes.Description: A guilty Darius is determined to protect the island's innocent dinos â€” even if he has to do it all alone. But with luck, maybe he won't have to...

Episodes.Title: View from the Top
Episodes.Description: The campers catch a lift to Lookout Point in search of materials to make a sail, then must quickly find a way back down. Ben worries about leaving Bumpy.

Episodes.Title: Safe Harbor
Episodes.Description: After finding Mitch and Tiff's abandoned yacht, the happy campers celebrate. But the party's over when something big goes bump in the night.

Episodes.Title: Casa De Kenji
Episodes.Description: Kenji takes the campers to his father's penthouse to gather supplies â€” but they've soon got company. Sammy reflects on what life must be like back home.

Episodes.Title: Clever Girl
Episodes.Description: A thrilling chase brings Darius, Kenji and Yaz to the old Jurassic Park Visitors Center. Elsewhere on the island, Brooklynn and Sammy find a secret lab.

Episodes.Title: Eye of the Storm
Episodes.Description: Sammy and Brooklynn rush to warn the others about a sinister new threat while Darius, unaware of the danger, searches for his dad's favorite dinosaur.

Episodes.Title: The Long Run
Episodes.Description: As a poisoned camper fights to survive, it's up to Yaz â€” the fastest among them â€” to fetch the antidote before it's too late.

Episodes.Title: A Shock to the System
Episodes.Description: It's crunch time for the campers to get to the boat and make their escape... until Ben disappears, deciding he'd rather stay. Can Darius change his mind?

Episodes.Title: Escape from Isla Nublar
Episodes.Description: With multiple threats running rampant on the island, dinosaur lover Darius must put his feelings aside and make a difficult decision.

Episodes.Title: Whatever It Takes
Episodes.Description: The group is forced to switch gears when a familiar face returns to Isla Nublar. Now, getting off the island is no longer the most important thing.

Episodes.Title: Stay on Mission
Episodes.Description: With Brooklynn being held prisoner, the remaining campers hatch a plan to rescue her â€” and it won't be easy.

Episodes.Title: Beneath the Surface
Episodes.Description: Out at sea, the campers see sunny skies... then discover a stowaway on board. A surprise attack from the deep leaves them stranded on unfamiliar shores.

Episodes.Title: At Least...
Episodes.Description: The weary crew dodges danger in the desert while trying to figure out where they are. But they unearth more questions than answers.

Episodes.Title: Turning Dr. Turner
Episodes.Description: A strange tunnel takes the teens to a lush forest, where they meet a mysterious scientist studying dino behavior. The question is: Can they trust her?

Episodes.Title: Rude Awakening
Episodes.Description: With Dr. Turner's help, the campers hatch a plan to get off the island that finds them crossing a snowy arctic biome â€” and making a selfless rescue.

Episodes.Title: The Long Game
Episodes.Description: After learning the truth about Mae's boss, Sammy's ready to go rogue to take him down... just as Mae gets ready to confront him. Cue the killer robots!

Episodes.Title: Mission Critical
Episodes.Description: With Mae in serious condition and Kash's end game clear, the campers vow to save the dinosaurs and stop Mantah Corp. But evil BRADs are everywhere.

Episodes.Title: Staying Alive
Episodes.Description: Darius has to think fast to distract Kash and protect the others, so he pretends to hate dinos as much as Kash does â€” while learning everything he can.

Episodes.Title: Technical Difficulties
Episodes.Description: Brooklynn must devise a hack to help Darius, who's being tailed by an upgraded BRAD-X. Meanwhile, Kash prepares to woo a group of dangerous investors.

Episodes.Title: Dino-Sitting
Episodes.Description: Darius keeps Kash busy with competitive video gaming while the others break into the nursery. Yaz asks Brooklynn how she feels about Kenji.

Episodes.Title: Taking Control
Episodes.Description: Ben's refusal to bond with a new friend leads to regret â€” and a realization that it's time to take Kash down. Kenji and Brooklynn face their feelings.

Episodes.Title: Who's the Boss?
Episodes.Description: Just when it feels like things are getting back to normal, Kash's boss arrives on Mantah Corp. island and begins moving forward with a devastating plan.

Episodes.Title: Reunited
Episodes.Description: Kenji's thrilled to see his father - and eager to prove himself. Elsewhere, Sammy and Brooklynn team up to find out what happened to Sammy's family.

Episodes.Title: The Final Test
Episodes.Description: A cryptic clue prompts Brooklynn, Darius and Ben to dig into Mr. Kon's motives. Kenji plans a date with Brooklynn while helping his dad prep for a party.

Episodes.Title: Battle Lines
Episodes.Description: Kenji asks his friends to back off and stay out of his father's business. But to save the island's dinos, they're willing to risk breaking his trust.

Episodes.Title: Evasive Action
Episodes.Description: A stunning betrayal lands the friends in lockdown, where they unpack their feelings and plot their escape. Kenji follows his father to Isla Nublar.

Episodes.Title: Shaky Ground
Episodes.Description: Something unsettling is sending the dinos into a frenzy. Darius and Brooklynn pour their energies into problem-solving. Kenji chooses sides.

Episodes.Title: Out of the Pack
Episodes.Description: Kenji accepts an important assignment - and drives straight into danger. Back on Mantah Corp. Island, the others race to ruin Mr, Kon's plans.

Episodes.Title: The Leap
Episodes.Description: The Kids come up with a plan to protect the dinosaurs. Left on her own, Sammy will have to rely on her own strength. Yaz opens up to Ben.

Episodes.Title: Clean Break
Episodes.Description: An Increasingly suspicious Kenji starts looking into his father's activities. Mae works to break free from Kon's control and follow her heart.

Episodes.Title: The Core
Episodes.Description: Yaz is ready to tell Sammy the truth - but the island has other plans. A conflicted Darius worries that he's lost his way.

Episodes.Title: Arrival
Episodes.Description: The friends must think fast to outwit Mr. Kon and his cronies. Ben sets out to rescue an old friend - and gets help from a surprising source.

Episodes.Title: The Last Stand
Episodes.Description: A high-stakes battle begins for control of Mantah Corp. Island. Kenji's ready to rejoin his friends, but Darius isn't sure he can forgive him.

Episodes.Title: The Nublar Six
Episodes.Description: With the future of the Island at steak, the friends band together - and fight harder than ever before - to protect what's really important.
